## Overview

- Gateway between BZA and users
- [Flask](https://flask.palletsprojects.com/) application (Python 3-only, 3.7, originally Python 2-only)
- Replace [https://a.blazemeter.com](https://a.blazemeter.com) with [https://internal.customer.com](https://internal.customer.com)
- BZA's **account** entity [/api/v4/accounts/NNNNN](https://a.blazemeter.com/api/v4/accounts/NNNNN)
- **appUrl** field managed from [account environment settings](https://new-pc.blazemeter.com/app/#/settings/accounts/318192/environment) (ie. [https://internal.customer.com](https://internal.customer.com))
- Use [blueprints](https://github.com/Blazemeter/private-cloud/tree/master/app/bzm_gateway_interceptor/blueprint) or [handlers](https://github.com/Blazemeter/private-cloud/tree/master/private_cloud/handler) to proxy upstream
- [Scheduler](https://github.com/Blazemeter/private-cloud/blob/master/private_cloud/__main__.py#L26) is cooperative between BZA's scheduler and `bzm-app`'s own: ignore if payload differs from local copy
- Not necesarilly a 1:1 request/resonse
- Torero ([PC](https://github.com/Blazemeter/a.blazemeter.com/blob/develop/src/blazemeter/Controller/CraneComponents/ToreroComponent.php#L136))

